-- McGraw Hill posts 18 percent rise in quarterly profit
-- 
-- Thu Jul 25, 2013 7:23am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/07/25/us-mcgrawhill-results-idUSBRE96O0H720130725

 

 (Reuters) - Standard & Poor's owner McGraw Hill Financial Inc ( MHFI.N ) posted an 18 percent rise in quarterly profit as it earned more from its ratings agency and its Dow Jones indices. 
 The company, formerly known as McGraw-Hill Cos Inc, said net income increased to $254 million, or 91 cents per share, in the second quarter, from $216 million, or 76 cents per share, a year earlier. (Reporting by Tanya Agrawal and Varun Aggarwal in Bangalore; Editing by Saumyadeb Chakrabarty)